---
// GDPR (EU 2016/679) privacy page draft. Before launch:
//   1. Fill every [BRACKET] slot. The controller is whoever legally runs the site.
//   2. Make section 3 match reality: pick the self-hosted OR cloud Plausible
//      wording, or delete the analytics paragraphs entirely if the site ships
//      without analytics (then also trim the meta description below).
//   3. German-market sites: translate this page into German (Datenschutzerklaerung)
//      and serve it at /datenschutz; German law expects legal pages in German.
//   4. A solid baseline, not legal advice. When in doubt, have it reviewed.
// The copy below already passes the a11y / seo / tone / email suites: keep one
// <h1>, the description in the 120-160 char window, no em dashes or banned
// contractions, and every email address behind <EmailLink>.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import EmailLink from '../components/EmailLink.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${SITE.name} handles personal data: cookieless analytics, hosting on Cloudflare Pages, contact data handling, and your rights under the GDPR.`}>
  <section class="wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      Last updated: [DATE]. This page explains which personal data this website
      processes, on what legal basis under the GDPR (EU 2016/679), and which
      rights you have.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <p>Responsible for data processing on this website:</p>
    <p>
      [CONTROLLER LEGAL NAME]<br />
      [STREET AND NUMBER]<br />
      [POSTCODE, CITY, COUNTRY]<br />
      Contact: <EmailLink address="hello@example.com" subject="Privacy request" />
    </p>

    <h2>2. Hosting and server logs</h2>
    <p>
      This site is served by <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> (Cloudflare, Inc.,
      101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When you visit a page,
      Cloudflare processes technical connection data (IP address, date and time,
      requested URL, browser user agent) to deliver the site and to protect it
      against attacks. The legal basis is our legitimate interest in operating a
      secure and fast website (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). Cloudflare acts as our
      processor under Art. 28 GDPR; transfers to the USA are covered by the
      EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and standard contractual clauses. We do not
      combine these logs with any other data.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Cookies and analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This website is ad-free and <strong>sets no cookies</strong>. Your visit
      leaves no advertising or cross-site tracking identifiers with us.
    </p>
    <p>
      To understand how the site is used, we run <strong>Plausible
      Analytics</strong>, a privacy-friendly measurement tool
      [self-hosted on our own server / operated for us by Plausible Insights
      O&Uuml;, V&auml;striku tn 2, 50403 Tartu, Estonia (EU)]. It is cookieless
      and collects no personal data. It does not track you across websites or
      over time, and no data is shared with third parties. Visitor IP addresses
      are processed only transiently to derive anonymous, aggregated counts and
      are never stored. The resulting metrics (such as page views, referrers and
      countries) are aggregated and cannot be traced back to an individual.
    </p>
    <p>
      The legal basis for this aggregated measurement is our legitimate interest
      in operating and improving the website (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). Because the
      measurement is cookieless and stores no personal data, no consent banner is
      required. You can prevent the measurement entirely by blocking the
      analytics script in your browser.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Contact by email</h2>
    <p>
      If you contact us, we process the data you provide (name, email address,
      and the content of your message) to handle the request and possible
      follow-up questions. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR where the request
      relates to a contract, otherwise our legitimate interest in answering
      enquiries (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). We keep the correspondence only as long as
      needed for this purpose and for any statutory retention duties.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR you have the right of access (Art. 15), rectification
      (Art. 16), erasure (Art. 17), restriction of processing (Art. 18), data
      portability (Art. 20), and objection to processing based on legitimate
      interest (Art. 21). To exercise any of these rights, contact us via the
      address in section 1; we will verify your identity before acting on a
      request. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a data
      protection supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes to this page</h2>
    <p>
      We will update this page whenever the data processing on this site
      changes, and adjust the date at the top accordingly.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
